<F P=101> GUATEMALA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bombs Rock Capital Prior To Resumption of Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bombs Rock Capital Prior To Resumption of Peace Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Boutique, Toruno's Home Hit </H4>

<F P=102> PA0106044394 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0416 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0106044394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 31 May (NOTIMEX) -- Unidentified 
individuals tonight detonated two bombs in different places in 
Guatemala City, according to the volunteer fire department. 
  The fire department chief, Emilio Najera, told NOTIMEX that 
one of the bombs exploded in front of the home of the brother of 
Monsignor Rodolfo Quezada Toruno, bishop of Zacapa and the 
former mediator in negotiations between the government and the 
guerrillas. The second bomb went off at Climat, a store located 
in the exclusive Zone 9 of this capital. 
  Firemen did not specify the type of explosives used in the 
attacks, both of which caused considerable damage but no 
casualties. The attacks were carried out on the Day of 
Constitutionality, just 24 hours before the peace talks between 
the government and the Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity 
(URNG) are due to resume in Mexico. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

