JPRS 
Terrorism 

</HEADER>

<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   29 May 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jordanian Authorities Release Abu-Nidal Group Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jordanian Authorities Release Abu-Nidal Group Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2905181294 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 29 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2905181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fatah-the Revolutionary Council group, led by 
Abu-Nidal [Sabri al-Banna], has announced that Jordan has 
released some of its members who were accused of involvement in 
the assassination of a Jordanian diplomat, Na'ib al-Ma'ayitah, 
in Beirut in January. The group, however, did not specify the 
number of the detainees who were released. 
  The Jordanian police on 25 February announced that it 
arrested 25 members of Fatah-the Revolutionary Council within 
the context of this case. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

