<H3> <TI>   Device in Scrap Metal Shop Kills One </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Device in Scrap Metal Shop Kills One </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2905060594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2250 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2905060594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 May (MENA)--Citizen Ahmad 'Abd-al-'Aziz 
Ahmad was killed and his father injured when a strange object 
exploded while they were buying scrap metal from Sabri Sayyid 
Abu-Zayd, a scrap metal dealer in the eastern part of al-Qanatir 
al-Khayriyah. 
  A responsible security source from the Interior Ministry 
stated that the incident took place in the town of Kafr 
al-Dawwar at 1430 when the two citizens were inspecting various 
pieces of metal. They found a strange metal object which looks 
like the armature of a car with a wire attached to it. Upon 
pulling the wire, the metal piece exploded. 
  The salesman gathered the three similar-looking pieces and 
threw them into the water canal. Security men retrieved and 
detonated them. 
  The security source said it is clear that these metal 
objects 
are explosives marked with "45 military offensive." The metal 
pieces have been seized. 
  A report has been prepared on the incident and the northern 
military region of Alexandria has been notified so an explosives 
expert can come down to take the necessary measures regarding 
the seized bombs. 

</TEXT>

