  [Excerpts] 'Allamah Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah has stated 
that at this stage we must not preoccupy ourselves with talking 
about the state's responsibility regarding the Israeli Army's 
kidnapping of al-Hajj Mustafa al-Dirani, but we must think 
quietly about how to respond. 
  In his Friday sermon, which he delivered at Imam al-Rida 
Mosque in B'ir al-'Abd [southern suburb of Beirut], Fadlallah 
said: Our brother al-Hajj Mustafa al-Dirani was kidnapped on 
the night of 'Id al-Adha. When we study this issue, we find it 
is a victory for Israel over all the various forces on the 
ground. There were political, security, and military gaps. We 
have discovered something about this country as far as the 
mentality of the government. This government does not respect 
its people. This government is not prepared to forgo its 
comfort and look after the citizen's interests. [passage omitted] 
  We must think quietly how to respond. You know that the 
resistance's arm is long. The enemy foreign minister said that 
Israel's arm is long. When Israel assassinated Sayyid 'Abbas 
al- Musawi, the strugglers taught him that their arm reached 
Israel in Argentina. The battle is as big as the world and as 
long as the length of time. We will work with all 
responsibility as Muslim strugglers all over the world. 
  Fadlallah said that Israel did not only kidnap al-Dirani, it 
also kidnapped every Lebanese citizen. It kidnapped the state, 
the government, and the people. 

