<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   3 June 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> YEMEN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa Source Denies Iraqis Engaged in Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa Source Denies Iraqis Engaged in Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0306111094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1030 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0306111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source has categorically denied that 
any Arab party is participating in the military operations waged 
by the forces of legitimacy against rebellious secessionists. 
The source described the reports disseminated by the 
secessionist gang that Iraqis are participating in the fighting 
as false, fabricated, and misleading allegations. This gang has 
repeated such fabrications and lies to mislead public opinion 
and gain some Arab and international parties' sympathy, said the 
source. 
  The responsible source added: It is not new to see this gang 
repeating such false allegations on the presence of Iraqis or 
others. Yesterday, the television, which is controlled by this 
gang, showed Sudanese nurse Salah Muhammad Fadlallah and claimed 
that he is a pilot fighting at the side of the forces of unity 
and legitimacy. This allegation was exposed when the gang 
presented the documents of this person who was kidnapped by the 
members of this gang from his work site in one of the medical 
centers in the Lahij Governorate. This person, who has been 
working as a nurse in Yemen for the past five years, was shown 
on the television as a pilot. 

</TEXT>

