<H3> <TI>   Russian Border Troop Officer Killed in Dushanbe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Border Troop Officer Killed in Dushanbe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105081694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0718 
GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105081694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Excerpt] Dushanbe, 31 May -- Lieutenant Colonel Vladimir 
Borisenkov, a senior member of the Russian Federation border 
troops staff in Tajikistan, became the latest victim of 
terrorists in Dushanbe today. 
  The ITAR-TASS correspondent learned from the staff of 
Russian 
Federation border troops in Tajikistan that Vladimir Borisenkov 
was fatally wounded by unidentified people while carrying out 
his duties at about 0730 [0230 GMT]. The officer died some time 
later in a military hospital without regaining consciousness. 
  A judicial investigation into the crime has begun. 
  Lt. Col. Vladimir Borisenkov had worked on the staff of the 
Russian Federation border troops since 1980. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

