  [Text] INTERFAX has reported that Chechen Interior Minister 
Magomet Eldiyev, his deputy Said Alibatayev, and their driver 
were killed in a car crash on the night of 27 May. According to 
unconfirmed reports, the minister's car exploded a mine 20 
kilometers west of Groznyy. 

