<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explodes on Train Coming From Georgia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Explodes on Train Coming From Georgia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306142594 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0807 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0306142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan ("LRAGIR," "RESPUBLICA ARMENIA" dailies), 
06/03/94 -- A regular explosion blew in a carriage of the train 
heading to Armenia, between the Sadakhlo and Ayrum stations (on 
Georgian territory) at 10:30am yesterday morning. 
  "LRAGIR" reports, the bomb was mounted in one of the freight 
carriages of the train. The explosion damaged the carriage, 
loaded with mazut (heating oil 1-4), but fire has been prevented. 
  According to "RESPUBLICA ARMENIA," 60 tons of fuel spilled 
out and cleaning operations are currently carried out at the 
railroad to restore movement of trains. 
  Spokesman of RA [Republic of Armenia] Special Affairs State 
Department A.Melkoumian informed "LRAGIR" that the railway 
wasn't damaged and movement of trains continues. 

</TEXT>

