<H3> <TI>   Greek Spokesman Denies Turkish Kurd's Confession on Training </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greek Spokesman Denies Turkish Kurd's Confession on Training </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306164894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0306164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said that 
Turkey continues to carry out a slanderous campaign against 
Greece and to bring unfounded charges by invoking events which 
are obviously contrary to the reality. The spokesman made the 
above statement when he was asked about the government's comment 
regarding the confession of the Kurdish fighter who was tortured 
by Turkish authorities to say that he had been trained at a camp 
for terrorists in Greece. Once again Venizelos underlined that 
our country will not contribute to the effort to cultivate false 
tension. We call on Turkey, the spokesman said, to stop 
implicating Greece in its internal problems. The Greek state 
authority, Venizelos stressed, controls the whole of its 
territory which is open and accessible to everyone, especially 
to journalists. Finally, the government spokesman expressed the 
government's regret for the confirmation of brutal violation of 
human rights, such as in the case of detained persons subjected 
to torture to sign forged confessions. 

</TEXT>

