<H3> <TI>   Dev-Sol, Islamic Group Members Caught in Ankara </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dev-Sol, Islamic Group Members Caught in Ankara </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0106072794 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2000 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0106072794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Thirteen members of an illegal leftist organization 
and four members of a radical religious organization were caught 
in Ankara. In a news conference, Ankara Security Director Orhan 
Tasanlar said that the suspects belonging to Dev-Sol 
[Revolutionary Left] posted placards, distributed pamphlets, and 
threw Molotov cocktails on various dates. Tasanlar reported 
that the suspects belonging to the illegal Islamic Great 
Vanguards Front [Islami Buyuk Akincilar Cephesi] threw bombs at 
various places in Ankara. One pistol, large quantities of 
material used in the manufacturing of time bombs, and 
organizational documents were also seized. 

</TEXT>

