<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Guerrilla Activities Through 8 June </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Guerrilla Activities Through 8 June </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0906022394 </F>
<F P=103> PA0906022394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Colombian guerrilla activities monitored through 8 
June. 
  An attack perpetrated on the morning of 2 June by 30 members 
of the Army of National Liberation (ELN) against the police 
station and the mayor's office in Villa del Rosario, 10 km 
southeast of Cucuta, left three police officers dead and four 
others wounded. Property damage resulting from the attack has 
been estimated at more than 80 million pesos. Meanwhile, three 
trucks that were deployed to defend Villa del Rosario were 
ambushed by another group of guerrillas on the Cucuta-San 
Antonio road. Police also defused two bombs outside the mayor's 
office. (Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 3 Jun 94 p 13A) 
  Four guerrillas, members of the ELN's Camilo Torres Front, 
have been killed in clashes with the San Mateo Battalion in La 
Gloria and Pelaya, Cesar Department. Meanwhile, lawyer Roger 
Efrain Lorduy was released by rebels who had kidnapped him. One 
FAL rifle, two R-15 rifles, a fragmentation grenade, and other 
weapons were seized. Meanwhile, on 2 June, a 
Cincelejo-Barranquilla bus was torched by 15 members of the 37th 
Front of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) in 
Ovejas, Sucre Department. (Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in 
Spanish 3 Jun 94 p 10A) 
  The 4th Brigade has reported that four military agents 
killed 
in a FARC ambush in Altos de la Cienega, Antioquia Department, 
will be buried today in Medellin. General Mario Hugo Galan said 
the attack took place as the military agents were implementing 
the Democracy Plan to guarantee the 19 June elections. One 
soldier was wounded during the ambush. (Santa Fe de Bogota 
Emisoras Caracol Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 7 Jun 94) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

