<H3> <TI>   Bomb Blast on Train Kills Two, Injures 25 in Madhya Pradesh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Blast on Train Kills Two, Injures 25 in Madhya Pradesh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0606032294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0606032294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two persons were killed and 25 others injured in a 
bomb explosion in a coach at the Delhi-bound Samta Express 
coming from Vishakhapatnam yesterday evening. The incident 
occurred near Rajnandgaon in Madhya Pradesh. Twelve of the 
injured persons were admitted to the Civil Hospital at 
Rajnandgaon, while others were discharged after first aid. The 
Central Railway Authorities have pressed into service their 
medical teams and are arranging a replacement for the affected 
coach. An emergency counter has been set up at Nagpur with 
phone numbers of 532417, repeat, 532417 and 532597, repeat, 
532597 to handle inquiries from relations of passengers and 
render assistance. A relief train has also been sent from 
Raipur to the site. 

</TEXT>

