94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Major General Uri Sagi, head of the IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] Intelligence Branch, said today that he believes 
that the basic goals of the PLO and Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement] will not change, although they are undergoing a 
pragmatic adaptation to the political reality. Our 
correspondent Yo'el Nir reports that Gen. Sagi made the remarks 
at the Knesset Foreign Affairs and Defense Committee. 
  Likud Chairman Binyamin Netanyahu said that he had obtained 
information from the defense establishment according to which 
the government intends to free 400 Hamas and Islamic Jihad 
activists, and inquired as to the impact this move would have on 
the security situation. Gen. Sagi said he cannot deny this 
information, adding that it is obvious that if those prisoners 
are released, some of them will engage in terror activity. 

