<H3> <TI>   Hizballah Kidnaps Seven Linked to al-Dirani Abduction </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hizballah Kidnaps Seven Linked to al-Dirani Abduction </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Retired Syrian General, Six Lebanese Held </H4>

<F P=102> NC0806202594 Paris AFP in English 2001 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0806202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ba'labakk, Lebanon, June 8 (AFP)--Pro-Iranian 
Hizballah guerrillas kidnapped six Lebanese and a retired Syrian 
soldier Wednesday in Syrian-controlled eastern Lebanon, police 
said. 
  Lebanese and Syrian security services had contacted the 
group 
late Wednesday in a bid to secure their release, they said. The 
seven were not identified. 
  Witnesses said that three people were beaten and seized from 
their homes by Hizballah members, while the four others were 
taken in public places in Ba'labakk and its surroundings. 
  Security services said the seven could have been taken in a 
Hizballah sweep to investigate the kidnapping on May 21 of 
pro-Iranian guerrilla leader Mustafa al-Dirani who was seized 
from his home in a raid by Israeli commandos. 
  Israel hopes al-Dirani can supply vital information on 
missing Israeli airman Ron Arad shot down in south Lebanon in 
1986. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

