Network in Russian 1700 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Several hours ago, a terrorist act was perpetrated 
in Moscow. Our correspondent D. Matyushin has just returned 
from the location. 
  Matyushin: There was a powerful explosion this 
afternoon at about 0500 hours, near Paveletskiy railway station, 
alongside the famous Logovaz company. Eyewitnesses stated that 
as Logovaz General Director Boris Berezovskiy was driving his 
car out of the gates, a nearby car stuffed with explosives blew 
up. The driver was killed and the director general's bodyguard 
was badly wounded. Boris Berezovskiy himself received burns to 
his face. He was in a state of shock and was taken to the 
hospital. A driver who was passing by at the time of the 
explosion was also hurt. The exploded empty car had Lithuanian 
license plates and a remote control device had been placed in 
it. According to Yuriy Kolpakov, head of the department of city 
procuracy, it was a planned attempt on the life of the director 
of Logovaz. 
  In Moscow alone in the past six months there have been 10 
such assassination attempts. [Video shows badly damaged car, 
people milling around street] [See "Selected Video Reports" 
section for information on ordering tape.] 

</TEXT>

