<TEXT>
to   Iran 

<F P=102> TA0806102494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2100 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0806102494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] President Suleyman Demirel 
replied to reporters' questions on various issues in Afyon 
today. In answer to a question on whether he had sent a letter 
to the Iranian President 'Ali Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani, Demirel 
said: Yes, I sent him a letter on the terrorism issue. 
  Pointing out that terrorist organizations are being squeezed 
as a result of security forces' operations, Demirel reiterated 
his call to those involved in terrorism to surrender. 
  Demirel stated that according to Turkey's observations, the 
terrorists mostly escaped to Iran. Explaining that Iranian 
officials show a lot of goodwill regarding this issue, Demirel 
recalled that the territory is very rugged. Demirel said the 
following regarding his letter to Rafsanjani: 
  [Begin Demirel recording] I know that Iran will not give 
protection to those murderers but, nevertheless, the information 
we have is that they are being given shelter in certain areas 
and I noted their names in my letter. The Iranian president has 
always greatly respected me and carefully considered what I say. 
I have informed Rafsanjani that Turkey is disturbed regarding 
this issue. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

