<H3> <TI>   Twelve Members of Illegal Islamic Group Caught in Ankara </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Twelve Members of Illegal Islamic Group Caught in Ankara </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0606182494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0606182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Twelve members of the illegal Islamic Great Eastern 
Raiders Front were caught in Ankara. According to a statement 
issued by the Ankara Security Directorate, security forces also 
seized 17 hand-written books stolen from the Amasya Sultan 
Beyazit Library. The income to be generated from the sale of 
the books, including a Koran written by the Prophet Osman, was 
to be used to finance the organization. 

