<F P=106> [Article by Richard Savill, Irish correspondent: "Workmen </F>
Shot Dead by Loyalist Terrorists"] 
  [Excerpt] Loyalist terrorists shot dead two Roman Catholic 
men and slightly injured another as they worked at a sheltered 
housing development in north Belfast yesterday. 
  The attack by the outlawed Ulster Volunteer Force took place 
as the Government planned its response to Sinn Fein's questions 
about future policy on Northern Ireland. 
  The two dead men, both electricians, one in his 40's and the 
other in his 20's, were believed to come from the mid-Ulster 
area. 
  Their names were not being released until relatives had been 
informed. 
  Witnesses said the men were hit by automatic fire during 
their lunchbreak as they sat in a car on a building site in the 
Tiger's Bay area of the city. 
  Police later made several arrests and seized firearms during 
raids in the area. 
  The murders bring to 17 the number of terrorist killings in 
the province in the past month. 
  [Passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

