<H3> <TI>   Loyalist Gunman Kills Student in Armagh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Loyalist Gunman Kills Student in Armagh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94WR0168A London THE TIMES in English 19 May 94 p 2 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94WR0168A </F>
<F P=104>  London THE TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article: "Loyalist Gunman Kills Teenage Student"] </F>
  [Text] A student died when a Loyalist gunman sprayed the 
offices of a taxi firm in the centre of Armagh city. The man 
pushed an elderly woman to one side and shot Gavin Patrick 
McShane, 17, as he played a gaming machine. Two other people 
were also hit, one seriously. A witness who found the three 
victims said: "Apparently the gunman had pointed the weapon at 
the girl despatcher, but the gun jammed." 
  The attack came as the Government continued to prepare its 
response to Sinn Fein's demand for clarification of the Downing 
Street peace declaration. But Seamus Mallon, the SDLP MP whose 
constituency offices are directly opposite the taxi firm, urged 
an early resumption of talks. He said: "If we have the courage 
of our own political convictions we should take that declaration 
and build upon it." 

</TEXT>

